<br>
it is a touchy spot.<br>
<br>
I do not believe Spells are any way shape or form analogous to Items.<br>
<br>
When a Melee Dings, they are getting automatic upgrades.<br>
New Disciplines.  And Higher Caps to Offensive Skills.  Thier output goes up automatically.<br>
<br>
They also got a FREE accross the board upgrade months ago in DPS output.  ((2H weapon inc, and upped skill caps))<br>
<br>
When a caster dings, spell casting skills don't make you more efficient.  58 Druids and 54 Druid use same Fire Damage Output.<br>
<br>
I agree focus items, may require several upgrades.  And be like a weapon.  But spells no.<br>
<br>
Theres &quot;1&quot; way in the game for a 60 druid to up thier damage.<br>
Theres &quot;X&quot; numbers for any melee.<br>
<br>
I'll go the opposite I think ALL spells should be vendor sold.<br>
OR all melee disciplines should be put on a &quot;scroll&quot; that taught you how to do it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
